"{\"uid\": \"gjsentinel.com-news-western_colorado-law-enforcement-officers-support-special-olympics-article_37ff88da-238d-11ef-9c32-7bcce1a141d6.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  The Special Olympics Colorado State Summer Games will begin at 7:30 p.m. tonight at Bergman Field on the Colorado Mesa University campus.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Mesa_University\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.5243387240967838e-12, \"text\": \"Colorado Mesa\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Mesa_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado_Mesa_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the support that fuels these games has been forthcoming for many years.\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Law enforcement agencies across the country have supported the Special Olympics through a program called the Law Enforcement Torch Run since 1981.\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0146498722823817e-25, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_Enforcement_Torch_Run\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Law Enforcement Torch Run\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_Enforcement_Torch_Run\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_Enforcement_Torch_Run\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Various agencies host events each year tailored to their individual communities.\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The goal is to raise awareness and funds for the Special Olympics.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 494, \"end\": 510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0146498722823817e-25, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Grand Valley, the Mesa County Sheriff's Office hosts the annual Glow N Games to raise money for the Special Olympics.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 620, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0146498722823817e-25, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The focal point of the Glow N Games is a 5K run after dark.\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Participants wear bright clothing and use color powder and black lights to glow as they run.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The event was more than a run with other activities available like lawn games, bouncy houses and food trucks.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The goal is to create an event that is inclusive to the whole community  This year's Glow N Games took place this on June 1 at Long Family Park.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About 100 people raced in the 5K and the event raised more than $18,000 for the Special Olympics, more than in previous years.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0146498722823817e-25, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This year was a very successful year\\\" said Lt. Wade Pacheco of the Sheriff's Office.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9925471559390938, \"rank\": 0.007508806021121327, \"text\": \"Sheriff\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pacheco has been involved in organizing this event since it was started in 2017.\", \"from\": 1262, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, the very next year, the Mesa County Sheriff's Office received the Agency of the Year Award.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, the MCSO was inducted into the Special Olympics Hall of Fame for its work, fundraising and commitment to Special Olympics.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0146498722823817e-25, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Image byJill HeyerfromPixabay  These awards demonstrate MCSO's commitment to give back to the community.\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1681, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's really a privilege to be able to work with the athletes and cheer them on and be a part of their celebration when they receive their medals,\\\" Pacheco said.\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Glow N Games was a successful event, but that's not the only event that the MCSO will be hosting this year.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1846, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/What_Now_(Sylvan_Esso_album)\", \"score\": 0.7603847835593146, \"rank\": 0.2535940195514395, \"text\": \"The Glow\", \"types\": [\"Q482994\", \"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/What_Now_(Sylvan_Esso_album)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/What_Now_(Sylvan_Esso_album)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beginning at 7:30 a.m. this morning - until supplies run out - the Sheriff's Office will be selling donuts to celebrate National Donut Day.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 2097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9925471559390938, \"rank\": 0.007508806021121327, \"text\": \"Sheriff\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of the proceeds will go to the Special Olympics.\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2133, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0146498722823817e-25, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyone who wants to purchase donuts can get them drive-thru style from the Sheriff's Office at 215 Rice St..\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9925471559390938, \"rank\": 0.007508806021121327, \"text\": \"Sheriff\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This event \\\"plays on the cops and donuts\\\" stereotype for a good cause, Pacheco said.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other events include the \\\"tip-a-cop\\\" fundraiser hosted by law enforcement agencies across the Grand Valley.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Sheriff's Office has worked with various police departments to raise money at restaurants by assisting waitstaff, bussing tables and serving food.\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2459, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9925471559390938, \"rank\": 0.007508806021121327, \"text\": \"Sheriff\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheriffs_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This event will take place in the coming months.\", \"from\": 2607, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This weekend, law enforcement agents from around the state will attend the State Summer Games to support athletes and hand out awards.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyone who is able to volunteer at this event is encouraged to sign-up through the Special Olympics Colorado website athttps://specialolympicsco.org/event/statesummergames/  Chance of Rain:49%  Sunrise:07:18:21 AM  Sunset:04:51:32 PM  Humidity:84%  Wind:E@6 mph  UV Index:0 Low  Variable clouds with snow showers.\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 3106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2893, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"score\": 0.9999815246225405, \"rank\": 1.5092302721364546e-05, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"dbpedia\": \"http:/